message:
Hi Stephen, thanks for the best intro to async/await.  

Is it legitimate to use the following instead of await Task.WhenAll(tasks)  

System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ConfiguredTaskAwaitable consumer = WriteTradesAsync(target, cancellationToken).ConfigureAwait(false);  

System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ConfiguredTaskAwaitable producer = ReadTradeWrapperAsync(target, cancellationToken).ConfigureAwait(false);  

await consumer;  
await producer;  

?  

Why this scenario also work? Shouldn't it wait for consumer to complete and only then begin to run and wait for the producer?
